column45: RHL no waves at collection site but waves breaking starting halfway to Lipoa Point, light rain the night before
Very windy at the parking lot (4-5), not so much at the beach (3)
KCP warning sign posted for bacteria
stream was dredged, anticipating tropical storm
Raul Ruiz (NMS)  tagged along as observer
Multimeter was shutting off at 30% power @ KWP site, changed batteries and had no prob
Took 4th reading, 20 in water were surfers
surfers and SUP peeps in water
dog on a surfboard & in water
nice and calm everywhere, flat, no wind
KKP - Beach fisherman reeling in fish.  Noticed blood trail from fish after sample taken
NMP - Construction - Hotel being built about 100' south of sample site
KKS - Water much clearer 20' from shore
KKP - 2 surfers coming to shore next to sampling
lots of fishing rods in the water but did not see any fisherpersons
lots of fishing rods in the water but did not see any fisherpersons but only 1 fisherman
tide was very high during sampling. (note about original comment: low tide was at 9:03 AM that day.  Could this comment have been referring to surf being high?)
took 4th reading of 12.2: 2nd DO reading was the same
